flowRoot.flowPara: Each robot is challenged with manipulating as many 'tokens' to have their colour on top. One game point is awarded for each token with the robot's colour on top and a further one awarded if it is within its corner area. There are four robots and nine tokens per match.

League points are awarded at the end of a three minute match as follows: 8 league points for the robot with the most game points, 4 for the second, 2 for the third and 1 league point for the robot with the fewest game points. Tied robots will be awarded the average of the points for their finishing positions - e.g. robots tied for first and second place will be awarded (8+4)÷2 = 6 league points.

The competition will start with a league which will last until early on Sunday afternoon. The results from the league will be used to seed teams in subsequent rounds of knockout matches, culminating with the final at the end of Sunday.
Doors open at 9:00 on both days. League matches run from 11:15 to 17:30 on Saturday and 9:30 to 14:45 on Sunday. Knockout matches begin at 15:00, with the final taking place at 16:45.
